<div id="review_178946064" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/178946064" />
    <a title="EAL" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2366630-eal"><img alt="EAL" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/178946064?book_show_action=true">Jun 22, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="EAL" class="user" itemprop="url" name="EAL" href="/user/show/2366630-eal">EAL</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2366630-eal?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2366630-eal?shelf=action-adventure">action-adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2366630-eal?shelf=protagonist-club">protagonist-club</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer178946064" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14034925849355538407">The first time I read this book I was ten and I did not like it at all. Things have changed.<br/><br/>10-year-old me: Computers? In <i>my</i> fantasy book? Sacre bleu!<br/><br/>14-year-old me: Magic + technology = pretty damn cool. Refreshing.<br/><br/>10yom: Multiple magic systems? Booooo.<br/><br/>14yom: Multiple magic systems? Awesome layering effect.<br/><br/>10yom: Roddy and Nick are both unheroic heroes who whine!<br/><br/>14yom: It&apos;s interesting how characters who are perfectly sympathetic when viewed from within their own POV can seem difficult or annoy</span>
  <span id="freeText14034925849355538407" style="display:none">The first time I read this book I was ten and I did not like it at all. Things have changed.<br /><br />10-year-old me: Computers? In <i>my</i> fantasy book? Sacre bleu!<br /><br />14-year-old me: Magic + technology = pretty damn cool. Refreshing.<br /><br />10yom: Multiple magic systems? Booooo.<br /><br />14yom: Multiple magic systems? Awesome layering effect.<br /><br />10yom: Roddy and Nick are both unheroic heroes who whine!<br /><br />14yom: It's interesting how characters who are perfectly sympathetic when viewed from within their own POV can seem difficult or annoying from the other person's POV. Besides, their shortcomings are realistic. And their descriptions of what it's like to be disliked/looked down upon/hated/disdained strike uncomfortably close to home - a sure sign of strong characterization.<br /><br />10yom: <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Grundo was just casting a glamor on Roddy the whole time?? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> Copout! Irrelevant! Distracting!<br /><br />14yom: Um. Kinda. Though the reveal of this does add a layer to Roddy's insecurity. This revelation could have come at a later time, though.<br /><br />10yom: Random plot threads! Digressions! RAEG!<br /><br />14yom: In the earlier part of the book it is rather difficult to see the big picture. It's only at the end that there's cohesiveness - and, as Nick noted, it's interesting to see how small things caused big changes.<br /><br />10yom: <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Why didn't <i>anyone</i> realize it was a different Merlin??? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />14yom: ...that's a fair point.<br /><br />10yom: I didn't like the ending line.<br /><br />14yom: I didn't either.<br /><br />10yom: This book was boooooring.<br /><br />14yom: No, it wasn't. It was actually pretty interesting. And you, dear younger self, are a brat. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14034925849355538407" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


