<span id="freeTextContainer704183019971182249">What better way to start the year than with one of my all-time favorite books? Diana Wynne Jones has written some fantastic books, and The Merlin Conspiracy does not disappoint. Every time, I&apos;m surprised by each new detail I find in the plot of this intricately spun story. Highly recommend this to anyone who loves other worlds, magical creatures, mythology based magic, and having separate narrators whose stories suddenly and dramatically connect. Add in a dose of evil moms, living cities, scary </span>
  <span id="freeText704183019971182249" style="display:none">What better way to start the year than with one of my all-time favorite books? Diana Wynne Jones has written some fantastic books, and The Merlin Conspiracy does not disappoint. Every time, I'm surprised by each new detail I find in the plot of this intricately spun story. Highly recommend this to anyone who loves other worlds, magical creatures, mythology based magic, and having separate narrators whose stories suddenly and dramatically connect. Add in a dose of evil moms, living cities, scary magical grandfathers, nice magical grandfathers, weird systems of government, and an extremely dislikable pair of twins (with matching names) to get an altogether exciting and fun book!</span>
