        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer96074592" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11227456965391641537">An expert bit of YA fantasy. Well paced, well plotted, appealing (and repulsive) characters, and all the threads nicely tied off at the end - which might be why I liked, and not loved, the book. Maybe that&apos;s one of the things that differentiates the adult-me reader from the child-me; I&apos;m happier now with a more ambiguous ending.<br/><br/>I&apos;m not sure I&apos;ll become a DWJ fan, but I&apos;m certainly an admirer.</span>
  <span id="freeText11227456965391641537" style="display:none">An expert bit of YA fantasy. Well paced, well plotted, appealing (and repulsive) characters, and all the threads nicely tied off at the end - which might be why I liked, and not loved, the book. Maybe that's one of the things that differentiates the adult-me reader from the child-me; I'm happier now with a more ambiguous ending.<br /><br />I'm not sure I'll become a DWJ fan, but I'm certainly an admirer.</span>
